35	IP Address for non-logged in users is always 127.0.0.1 when deployed behind a proxy (e.g. on ckan.net)	rgrp	rgrp	"When IP address is used to identify non-logged in users (for example on create and editing of packages) it is always 127.0.0.1 when using a reverse proxy (standard deployment configuration on a production machine and used e.g. on http://www.ckan.net).

This could be corrected by using HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR when available."	defect	closed	minor	v0.4	ckan	fixed				
